---
import ClientReportLayout from '../../../layouts/ClientReportLayout.astro';
---

<ClientReportLayout title="Website Health Report" clientName="Nexvel Solutions">
<!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="badge">AI-Powered Website Audit</span>
      <h1>Website Audit Report</h1>
      <div class="url">nexvelsolutions.com</div>
      <div class="date">April 3, 2026 &middot; Prepared by James &middot; Brothers Automate</div>

      <!-- Score Ring -->
      <div class="score-ring-container">
        <div class="score-ring">
          <svg width="200" height="200" viewBox="0 0 200 200">
            <circle class="bg" cx="100" cy="100" r="88" />
            <circle class="fg" cx="100" cy="100" r="88"
              stroke-dasharray="553"
              stroke-dashoffset="553" />
          </svg>
          <div class="score-text">
            <div class="score-number">42</div>
            <div class="score-label">out of 100</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Category Scores -->
      <div class="stats-bar">
        <div class="stat-card">
          <span class="stat-number score-low">2/10</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Content Freshness</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <span class="stat-number score-mid">5/10</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Meta & Titles</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <span class="stat-number score-low">3/10</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Image SEO</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <span class="stat-number score-mid">5/10</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Heading Structure</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <span class="stat-number score-low">2/10</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Technical SEO</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-card">
          <span class="stat-number score-mid">6/10</span>
          <span class="stat-label">Internal Linking</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- NAV -->
  <nav class="phase-nav">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="phase-nav-inner">
        <button class="phase-btn active" onclick="scrollToSection('overview')">Overview</button>
        <button class="phase-btn" onclick="scrollToSection('methodology')">Methodology</button>
        <button class="phase-btn" onclick="scrollToSection('findings')">Detailed Findings</button>
        <button class="phase-btn" onclick="scrollToSection('actions')">Action Plan</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <!-- OVERVIEW -->
  <section id="overview">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="exec-card animate-in">
        <h3>Executive Summary</h3>
        <p>
          Nexvel Solutions' website has significant SEO and content issues that are costing the business organic traffic and leads. Our analysis confirms the site ranks for just <strong>13 keywords</strong> (mostly branded) with an estimated <strong>~79 monthly visits</strong> -- while <a href="https://seolocale.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:underline;">SEO Locale</a> ranks for <strong>3,656 keywords</strong> with <strong>311x more traffic</strong>. A full 41-page site crawl revealed the homepage has <strong>no H1 tag</strong>, 14 pages return 301 redirects, and a test page is publicly accessible. SERP analysis shows Nexvel doesn't appear in the <strong>top 100 results</strong> for "SEO company Philadelphia," "web design Philadelphia," or "managed IT services Philadelphia." Google Maps shows they're <strong>not in the top 10</strong> for "digital marketing agency Elkins Park" and at <strong>position 51</strong> for "IT support Elkins Park" -- in their own hometown. They have <strong>7 Google reviews</strong> vs <a href="https://needmomentum.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:underline;">Momentum Digital</a>'s 155. Instagram: <strong>69 followers</strong>. Facebook: <strong>102 likes</strong>. For a marketing agency, this is an existential visibility problem across <strong>17,000+ monthly searches</strong> in target keywords.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Top Findings -->
      <div class="top-findings animate-in">
        <h3 style="margin-bottom:1rem;">Top Findings at a Glance</h3>

        <div style="background:var(--bg-surface);border-radius:var(--radius-lg);padding:0.5rem 1.5rem;box-shadow:var(--shadow);">
          <div class="top-finding-row">
            <div class="top-finding-icon">&#128200;</div>
            <div class="top-finding-text">
              <strong>13 keywords vs competitor's 3,656 -- 311x traffic gap</strong>
              <span><a href="https://seolocale.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:underline;">SEO Locale</a> (Jenkintown): ~24,583 visits. Zero commercial keywords ranked.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="priority-badge priority-critical">Critical</div>
          </div>
          <div class="top-finding-row">
            <div class="top-finding-icon">&#128205;</div>
            <div class="top-finding-text">
              <strong>Invisible on Google Maps in their own hometown</strong>
              <span>Not in top 10 for "digital marketing agency Elkins Park PA." Position 51 for "IT support Elkins Park PA." Only 7 Google reviews (4.9 stars) vs competitors with 100+.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="priority-badge priority-critical">Critical</div>
          </div>
          <div class="top-finding-row">
            <div class="top-finding-icon">&#128683;</div>
            <div class="top-finding-text">
              <strong>Blog abandoned since April 2020</strong>
              <span>Last post was about COVID-19. Other posts date to 2016. Zero content production for 6 years.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="priority-badge priority-critical">Critical</div>
          </div>
          <div class="top-finding-row">
            <div class="top-finding-icon">&#128200;</div>
            <div class="top-finding-text">
              <strong>Homepage statistics are outdated</strong>
              <span>Claims "3+ Billion Google Searches Per Day" -- the actual number is now 8.5+ billion.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="priority-badge priority-important">Important</div>
          </div>
          <div class="top-finding-row">
            <div class="top-finding-icon">&#128444;&#65039;</div>
            <div class="top-finding-text">
              <strong>Generic & placeholder images throughout</strong>
              <span>Alt text like "icon_01", "service_01". Multiple RevSlider dummy.png placeholders detected.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="priority-badge priority-critical">Critical</div>
          </div>
          <div class="top-finding-row">
            <div class="top-finding-icon">&#128269;</div>
            <div class="top-finding-text">
              <strong>No structured data / schema markup</strong>
              <span>Missing LocalBusiness schema for both office locations. Hurts local search visibility.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="priority-badge priority-critical">Critical</div>
          </div>
          <div class="top-finding-row">
            <div class="top-finding-icon">&#9888;&#65039;</div>
            <div class="top-finding-text">
              <strong>Title tag exceeds recommended length</strong>
              <span>"Web Design Philadelphia, SEO, Marketing & IT Support | Nexvel Solutions" is ~69 chars (limit: 60).</span>
            </div>
            <div class="priority-badge priority-minor">Minor</div>
          </div>
          <div class="top-finding-row">
            <div class="top-finding-icon">&#128205;</div>
            <div class="top-finding-text">
              <strong>No dedicated location pages</strong>
              <span>Two office addresses listed in footer but no SEO-optimized pages for each market.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="priority-badge priority-important">Important</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- METHODOLOGY -->
  <section class="flow-section" id="methodology">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header animate-in">
        <p class="eyebrow">Audit Methodology</p>
        <h2>How This Report Was Generated</h2>
        <p>AI-powered tools and data pipelines, from scrape to deliverable.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="flow-grid animate-in">
        <div class="flow-card">
          <div class="flow-icon flow-icon-blue">&#127760;</div>
          <h3>Scrape</h3>
          <p>Automated crawler extracted full page content, metadata, and structure</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
        <div class="flow-card">
          <div class="flow-icon flow-icon-purple">&#129504;</div>
          <h3>Analyze</h3>
          <p>AI analyzed content across 7 SEO categories with scoring</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
        <div class="flow-card">
          <div class="flow-icon flow-icon-amber">&#128202;</div>
          <h3>Score</h3>
          <p>Each category scored 1-10 with weighted overall score</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-arrow">&rarr;</div>
        <div class="flow-card">
          <div class="flow-icon flow-icon-green">&#128196;</div>
          <h3>Report</h3>
          <p>Formatted into client-ready report with action items</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Tools & Data -->
  <section style="background:var(--bg-surface-alt);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="meta-card animate-in" style="margin:0 auto;">
        <h3>Tools & Data Sources</h3>
        <table class="meta-table">
          <tr>
            <td>Web Scraping</td>
            <td>Automated web crawler extracted full page content, metadata, and site structure</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>AI Analysis Engine</td>
            <td><strong>Claude (Anthropic)</strong> -- Analyzed scraped content across 7 SEO categories, identified issues, and scored each area</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Competitive Intel</td>
            <td><strong>Web Search</strong> -- Cross-referenced Nexvel's online presence across Google, Yelp, Glassdoor, LinkedIn, and Crunchbase</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>SEO Data</td>
            <td>Automated SEO analysis across multiple data sources including keyword rankings, traffic estimation, competitor analysis, and site performance.</td>
          </tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="meta-card animate-in">
        <h3>Raw Data Extracted</h3>
        <table class="meta-table">
          <tr><td>CMS</td><td>WordPress 6.9.4 (behind Nginx/Cloudflare)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Slider Plugin</td><td>Slider Revolution 6.5.31</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Domain Rank</td><td><strong>401</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Ranked Keywords</td><td><strong>13 total</strong> (only 3 in top 10, all branded)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Est. Monthly Traffic</td><td><strong>~79 visits</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Traffic Value</td><td><strong>$107/month</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Performance</td><td><strong>71/100</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Accessibility</td><td><strong>82/100</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>SEO Score</td><td><strong>85/100</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Title Tag</td><td>Web Design Philadelphia, SEO, Marketing & IT Support | Nexvel Solutions <span style="color:var(--amber)">(69 chars)</span></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Meta Description</td><td>With offices in Philadelphia & Elkins Park, Nexvel helps grow & support local businesses... <span style="color:var(--green);">(good length)</span></td></tr>
          <tr><td>OG Tags</td><td>Present (title, description, image, URL)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Twitter Card</td><td>summary_large_image</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Last Modified</td><td>February 5, 2021 <span style="color:var(--red);">(5+ years ago)</span></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Robots</td><td>index, follow, max-image-preview:large</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Locations</td><td>325 Yorktown Plaza, Elkins Park, PA 19027 &middot; 1010 N Hancock St, Philadelphia, PA 19123</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Phone</td><td>215.885.8686</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Industries Served</td><td>Healthcare, Home Services, Legal, Retail, Automotive, Local Brands</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Partners</td><td>Jive, Moz Local, AWS, Google Partners</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Top Competitor</td><td><strong><a href="https://seolocale.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:underline;">SEO Locale</a></strong>: 3,656 keywords, ~24,583 ETV (311x more traffic)</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="meta-card animate-in">
        <h3>Production Pipeline (Gumloop)</h3>
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">This audit combines content analysis with live performance data. The entire process runs as an automated workflow:</p>
        <div class="pipeline-block">
          <span class="comment"># Gumloop Workflow: Website Audit Pipeline</span><br />
          <span class="input">INPUT</span> &nbsp;&rarr;&nbsp; User enters URL<br />
          <span class="node">NODE 1</span> &rarr;&nbsp; Crawler extracts page content &amp; metadata<br />
          <span class="node">NODE 2</span> &rarr;&nbsp; Analysis engine scores performance, keywords, &amp; competitors<br />
          <span class="ai">NODE 3</span> &rarr;&nbsp; AI analyzes across 7 SEO categories (scored)<br />
          <span class="ai">NODE 4</span> &rarr;&nbsp; AI formats professional client-ready report<br />
          <span class="input">NODE 5</span> &rarr;&nbsp; Save to Google Sheets (audit history)<br />
          <span class="input">NODE 6</span> &rarr;&nbsp; Draft email via Gmail with report attached<br />
          <span class="output">OUTPUT</span> &rarr;&nbsp; Branded audit report delivered
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DETAILED FINDINGS -->
  <section id="findings">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header animate-in">
        <p class="eyebrow">Detailed Findings</p>
        <h2>Category-by-Category Breakdown</h2>
        <p>Click any category to expand the full analysis.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="findings-list">

        <!-- Card 1: Content Freshness -->
        <div class="finding-card animate-in" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')">
          <div class="finding-header">
            <div class="finding-header-left">
              <div class="finding-status status-red"></div>
              <div class="finding-title">Content Freshness & Blog</div>
            </div>
            <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem;">
              <div class="finding-score score-low">2/10</div>
              <svg class="chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="finding-body">
            <h4>What We Found</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Most recent blog post: <strong>"Important Message To Our Customers About Coronavirus"</strong> -- dated April 2020</li>
              <li>Other blog posts date back to <strong>2016</strong> (SMX East recap, PPC+SEO article, reputation management)</li>
              <li>Only 4 blog posts visible on the homepage -- none in the last 6 years</li>
              <li>Homepage statistics cite "3+ Billion Google Searches Per Day" -- the actual number is now 8.5+ billion, suggesting the content hasn't been reviewed since ~2018</li>
            </ul>
            <h4>Why This Matters</h4>
            <p>Google rewards fresh, regularly updated content. For an agency that sells SEO services, having a dormant blog signals to both Google and potential clients that the site is on autopilot. Competitors with active blogs will outrank Nexvel for informational queries.</p>
            <h4>Recommendations</h4>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Immediate:</strong> Update or remove the COVID-19 post. Update homepage statistics to current numbers.</li>
              <li><strong>Short-term:</strong> Publish 2-4 blog posts per month targeting local SEO keywords (e.g., "web design Elkins Park", "SEO services Philadelphia").</li>
              <li><strong>Automation opportunity:</strong> Build an AI content pipeline that drafts SEO-optimized blog posts from keyword clusters, reducing production time from hours to minutes.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 2: Meta Tags -->
        <div class="finding-card animate-in" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')">
          <div class="finding-header">
            <div class="finding-header-left">
              <div class="finding-status status-yellow"></div>
              <div class="finding-title">Meta Tags & Title</div>
            </div>
            <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem;">
              <div class="finding-score score-mid">5/10</div>
              <svg class="chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="finding-body">
            <h4>What We Found</h4>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Title tag:</strong> "Web Design Philadelphia, SEO, Marketing & IT Support | Nexvel Solutions" -- 69 characters (recommended: under 60)</li>
              <li><strong>Meta description:</strong> "With offices in Philadelphia & Elkins Park, Nexvel helps grow & support local businesses with web development, creative design, marketing, & IT services." -- good length and content</li>
              <li>Open Graph tags are present and properly configured</li>
              <li>Twitter card is set to summary_large_image</li>
              <li>Robots meta allows indexing</li>
            </ul>
            <h4>Recommendations</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Shorten title tag to under 60 characters. Suggestion: <em>"Philadelphia Web Design, SEO & IT | Nexvel Solutions"</em> (52 chars)</li>
              <li>Add location-specific title tags for any service pages</li>
              <li>Ensure every page has a unique meta description (audit inner pages to verify)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 3: Heading Structure -->
        <div class="finding-card animate-in" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')">
          <div class="finding-header">
            <div class="finding-header-left">
              <div class="finding-status status-yellow"></div>
              <div class="finding-title">Heading Structure</div>
            </div>
            <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem;">
              <div class="finding-score score-mid">5/10</div>
              <svg class="chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="finding-body">
            <h4>What We Found</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>No explicit H1 tag detected -- the main heading "Hi, We're NeXVel" appears to be styled text rather than a semantic H1</li>
              <li>Multiple H2 tags are present and mostly descriptive</li>
              <li>H3/H4 hierarchy is reasonable but some headings are generic ("HEALTHCARE", "LEGAL" without context)</li>
              <li>Section headings are marketing-focused rather than keyword-optimized</li>
            </ul>
            <h4>Recommendations</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Add a proper H1 tag with the primary keyword (e.g., "Philadelphia Digital Marketing & IT Agency")</li>
              <li>Ensure only one H1 per page</li>
              <li>Add keyword-rich context to industry headings (e.g., "Healthcare Marketing Solutions" instead of just "HEALTHCARE")</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 4: Image Optimization -->
        <div class="finding-card animate-in" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')">
          <div class="finding-header">
            <div class="finding-header-left">
              <div class="finding-status status-red"></div>
              <div class="finding-title">Image Optimization</div>
            </div>
            <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem;">
              <div class="finding-score score-low">3/10</div>
              <svg class="chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="finding-body">
            <h4>What We Found</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Multiple images use <strong>generic alt text</strong>: "icon_01", "icon-healthcare", "service_01", "service_02", etc.</li>
              <li>At least <strong>5 instances of RevSlider's dummy.png</strong> placeholder image detected -- these are invisible placeholder files</li>
              <li>Client portfolio images use filenames like "client_king-1.jpg" without descriptive alt text</li>
              <li>Logo images have reasonable alt text ("Nexvel Solutions")</li>
              <li>No WebP format detected -- all images appear to be JPG/PNG (older, larger formats)</li>
            </ul>
            <h4>Recommendations</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Replace all generic alt text with descriptive, keyword-rich alternatives (e.g., "icon_01" to "Philadelphia healthcare marketing icon")</li>
              <li>Remove or replace all dummy.png placeholder references</li>
              <li>Convert images to WebP format for faster loading</li>
              <li>Add descriptive alt text to all client portfolio images</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 5: Technical SEO -->
        <div class="finding-card animate-in" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')">
          <div class="finding-header">
            <div class="finding-header-left">
              <div class="finding-status status-red"></div>
              <div class="finding-title">Technical SEO & Structured Data</div>
            </div>
            <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem;">
              <div class="finding-score score-low">2/10</div>
              <svg class="chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="finding-body">
            <h4>What We Found</h4>
            <ul>
              <li><strong style="color:var(--red);">No structured data / schema markup detected</strong> -- no LocalBusiness, Organization, or any JSON-LD schema</li>
              <li><strong>Performance: 71/100</strong> -- needs improvement (needs improvement across core metrics )</li>
              <li><strong>Accessibility: 82/100</strong> -- acceptable but with color contrast and heading order issues</li>
              <li><strong>SEO Score: 85/100</strong> -- title tag too long (69 chars), but crawlability and meta description pass</li>
              <li>Site infrastructure uses modern hosting</li>
              <li><strong>Domain Rank: 401</strong> with only <strong>13 ranked keywords</strong> and <strong>~79 estimated monthly visits</strong></li>
              <li><strong>Full site crawl (41 pages):</strong> 27 pages return 200, <strong>14 pages return 301 redirects</strong> from old URL structure</li>
              <li><strong>Homepage has NO H1 tag</strong> -- confirmed by full site crawl. 5 other pages also missing H1</li>
              <li>A <strong>test page ("test-yoast-gif")</strong> is publicly accessible and indexed</li>
              <li><strong>SSL certificate expires June 23, 2026</strong> (Let's Encrypt) -- needs renewal monitoring</li>
              <li><strong>Google Business Profile: 4.9 stars, only 7 reviews</strong> -- competitors have 100-155 reviews</li>
              <li><strong>Not in Google Maps top 10</strong> for "digital marketing agency Elkins Park PA" -- their HQ location</li>
              <li>Two physical locations listed but no dedicated location pages optimized for local search</li>
              <li>WordPress version 6.9.4 and RevSlider 6.5.31 -- need to verify these are the latest and fully patched</li>
              <li>Navigation uses anchor links (#home, #clients, #marketing-technology) -- search engines may not crawl these as separate pages</li>
              <li>The homepage is essentially a single-page design, limiting keyword targeting opportunities</li>
            </ul>
            <h4>Recommendations</h4>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Critical:</strong> Add LocalBusiness schema markup for both the Elkins Park and Philadelphia locations</li>
              <li>Create dedicated, SEO-optimized pages for each service category (web design, SEO, PPC, etc.)</li>
              <li>Create location-specific landing pages for each office</li>
              <li>Implement breadcrumb schema across all pages</li>
              <li>Audit WordPress and plugin versions for security vulnerabilities</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 6: Internal Linking -->
        <div class="finding-card animate-in" onclick="this.classList.toggle('open')">
          <div class="finding-header">
            <div class="finding-header-left">
              <div class="finding-status status-yellow"></div>
              <div class="finding-title">Internal Linking & Navigation</div>
            </div>
            <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem;">
              <div class="finding-score score-mid">6/10</div>
              <svg class="chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="finding-body">
            <h4>What We Found</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Main navigation has 6 items: Home, About, Services, Our Work, Careers, Contact</li>
              <li>Client portfolio links to individual case study pages (good)</li>
              <li>Multiple CTA buttons throughout ("Let's Get Started", "Contact Us", "Get a Free Consultation")</li>
              <li>Blog links exist but lead to extremely outdated content</li>
              <li>Footer contains duplicate navigation links plus social profiles</li>
              <li>Most internal links are anchor links on the same page rather than links to distinct pages</li>
            </ul>
            <h4>Recommendations</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Create dedicated service pages and link to them from the navigation (instead of anchor sections)</li>
              <li>Add contextual internal links within blog content (once new content is created)</li>
              <li>Add a sitemap page and ensure XML sitemap is submitted to Google Search Console</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ACTION PLAN -->
  <section id="actions" style="background:var(--bg-surface-alt);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header animate-in">
        <p class="eyebrow">Priority Action Plan</p>
        <h2>What to Fix First</h2>
        <p>Ranked by business impact -- what to fix first and what can be automated.</p>
      </div>

